&lt;p&gt;Marketing &amp;amp; Creative Operations enables Airbnb’s marketing and creative teams to operate as effectively and efficiently as possible. We strive to keep the team nimble: clarifying and establishing best practices, streamlining day-to-day processes, pivoting quickly to help retain focus on the work and our partner relationships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Difference You Will Make:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Airbnb is looking for a seasoned Creative Resourcing Lead to join Marketing &amp;amp; Creative Operations. This role is the operational heartbeat of our internal, multi-disciplinary creative studio — spanning advertising, design, photography, video, interactive, and social — and owns all facets of resource management: sourcing, onboarding, staffing, budget, and systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You thrive in the human side of resourcing creative talent, building deep knowledge of people&#39;s capabilities and motivations to match the right talent to the right work. You&#39;re calm under pressure, solutions-oriented, and as comfortable navigating ambiguity as you are running a tight process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Typical Day:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Head of Creative Operations, Global Production Director, and creative/production leads to anticipate and confirm staffing for active and upcoming projects — factoring in bandwidth, capabilities, career growth, and interests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and lead resourcing forums with Executive Producers and Creative Leads; ensure staffing charts, capacity, and assignments are always current and accurate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop relationships across the creative team to build an intimate understanding of individual capabilities and motivations; always balance immediate needs with long-term growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the end-to-end contract worker (CW) recruitment process, including CW recruiters, role tracking in Airtable, extension requests, and talent network development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Float and other resourcing tools — tracking all staffing and capacity for use in planning meetings and new project scoping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Tools Lead to build, maintain, and continuously improve resourcing infrastructure and processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead onboarding for all new full-time (FTE) and CW hires in partnership with the Senior Creative Operations Lead; run weekly onboarding calls to ensure smooth integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with creative leadership and Talent/HR on strategic hiring direction, diversity, and future growth planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Forecast and manage the full professional services and CW budget; provide monthly actualization and centralized reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate real-time, monthly, quarterly, and annual reporting on team output and resource utilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years in creative services, including 5+ years in a creative resource management or operations lead role (agency, studio, or in-house)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of creative workflow, skill sets, and staffing dependencies across disciplines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience with talent sourcing, capacity planning, budget management, and financial tracking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mastery of resourcing and project management tools (Float, Airtable, Excel/Google Sheets, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing and optimizing systems, processes, and workflows for creative organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional interpersonal skills — empathetic, diplomatic, and skilled at mediation and conflict resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to execute with precision and speed while managing multiple priorities in a fast-moving environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative, inventive, and calm under pressure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
